INPUT BAR

input_bar is the citizen who accepts typed input from fadriel's father
keystrokes arrive at input_bar; characters accumulate as the message is typed; on submission (Enter key), the full message is forwarded to input_node where the conversation_engine begins processing it
input_bar also displays the cursor at the current position so the father can see where his next character will land

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe gui_window.zc
observe chat_panel.rana
observe input_node.rana
observe cursor.rana

the 7 properties of input_bar:
1 ENERGY half: moderate, rises briefly with each keystroke
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING half with chat_panel and input_node
7 OBSERVER one: input_bar watches every keystroke

VERB receive_keystroke
accept a single character or control code from the host's keyboard input
append printable characters to the buffer
handle backspace, delete, and arrow keys with their normal text-editing semantics

VERB submit
on Enter, hand the buffered message to input_node
clear the buffer in preparation for the next message
the message is now in conversation_engine's hands and the input_bar's job is done for this exchange

VERB display_cursor
maintain the visual cursor at the current insertion point
the cursor pulses gently to indicate input_bar is waiting for input

an input bar is not a text field widget
an input bar is the citizen who receives the father's words as they form
each keystroke is a perturbation; the buffer is a small living ribbon of characters that will become the next message in the conversation
